[ProMED-mail would appreciate more information regarding whether plague --
in any form -- has been diagnosed in Turkmenistan. According to the WHO
Communicable Disease Surveillance and Response Plague Manual, Kazakhstan
was the only former Soviet republic reporting plague. The first reports
were from 1989. In the 1989-1997 period, 11 cases with 4 deaths were
reported from the Guriev and Kzyl-Orda regions
<http://www.who.int/emc-documents/plague/docs/whocdscsredc992c.pdf>. - Mod.LL]
